{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":484,"text":"I'm a historian."},{"time":1659,"text":"Steve told us about the future\nof little technology;"},{"time":5776,"text":"I'm going to show you some\nof the past of big technology."},{"time":9837,"text":"This was a project to build a 4,000-ton\nnuclear bomb-propelled spaceship"},{"time":15297,"text":"and go to Saturn and Jupiter."},{"time":17869,"text":"This took place in my childhood, 1957-65."},{"time":22564,"text":"It was deeply classified."},{"time":23867,"text":"I'm going to show you some stuff\nthat not only has not been declassified,"},{"time":27963,"text":"but has now been reclassified."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30493,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":34209,"text":"If all goes well, next year I'll be back,"},{"time":36277,"text":"and I'll have a lot more to show you,\nand if all doesn't go well,"},{"time":39432,"text":"I'll be in jail, like Wen Ho Lee."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41751,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":46486,"text":"So, this ship was basically\nthe size of the Marriott Hotel,"},{"time":50293,"text":"a little taller and a little bigger."},{"time":52600,"text":"And one of the people\nwho worked on it at the beginning"},{"time":55283,"text":"was my father, Freeman,\nthere in the middle."},{"time":57375,"text":"That's me and my sister, Esther,\nwho's a frequent TEDster."},{"time":60281,"text":"I didn't like nuclear\nbomb-propelled spaceships."},{"time":63467,"text":"I mean, I thought it was a great idea,\nbut I started building kayaks."},{"time":66756,"text":"So we had a few kayaks."},{"time":67944,"text":"Just so you know\nthat I am not Dr. Strangelove."}]},{"cues":[{"time":72159,"text":"But all the time I was out there\ndoing these strange kayak voyages"},{"time":75373,"text":"in odd, beautiful parts of this planet,"},{"time":78267,"text":"I always thought in the back\nof my mind about Project Orion,"},{"time":81600,"text":"and how my father and his friends\nwere going to build these big ships."},{"time":85600,"text":"They were actually going to go --"},{"time":87667,"text":"Ted Taylor, who led the project,\nwas going to take his children."},{"time":90728,"text":"My father was not going\nto take his children,"},{"time":92879,"text":"that was one of the reasons we sort\nof had a falling out for a few years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96542,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":100276,"text":"The project began in '57\nat General Atomics there,"},{"time":102800,"text":"that's right on the coast at La Jolla."},{"time":104766,"text":"Look at that central building\nright in the middle of the picture."},{"time":107863,"text":"That's the 130-foot diameter library."},{"time":111223,"text":"That is exactly the size\nof the base of the spaceship."},{"time":114200,"text":"So put that library\nat the bottom of that ship --"},{"time":116646,"text":"that's how big the thing was going to be."},{"time":118639,"text":"It would take two or three thousand bombs."},{"time":120709,"text":"The people who worked on it\nwere a lot of the Los Alamos people"},{"time":123710,"text":"who had done the hydrogen bomb work."},{"time":125459,"text":"It was the first project funded by ARPA."},{"time":127610,"text":"That's the contract where ARPA\ngave the first million dollars"},{"time":130497,"text":"to get this thing started."},{"time":131768,"text":"\"Spaceship project officially begun.\nJob waiting for you. Dyson.\""},{"time":135555,"text":"That's July '58."},{"time":137000,"text":"Two days later, the space traveler's\nmanifesto explaining why --"},{"time":141258,"text":"just like we heard yesterday --\nwhy we need to go into space:"},{"time":144160,"text":"\"... trips to satellites\nof the outer planets."},{"time":146351,"text":"August 20, 1958.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":148095,"text":"These are the statistics of what would be\nthe good places to go and stop."},{"time":152476,"text":"Some of the sizes of the ships,"},{"time":153989,"text":"ranging all the way up\nto ship mass of 8 million tons."},{"time":158195,"text":"So that was the outer extreme."},{"time":159652,"text":"Here was version two: 2,000 bombs."},{"time":163537,"text":"These are five-kiloton yield bombs,\nabout the size of small Volkswagens;"},{"time":168854,"text":"it would take 800 to get into orbit."},{"time":171337,"text":"Here we see a 10,000-ton ship\nwill deliver 1,300 tons"},{"time":175781,"text":"to Saturn and back --\nessentially, a five-year trip."},{"time":178619,"text":"Possible departure dates:\nOctober 1960 to February 1967."},{"time":183524,"text":"These are trajectories going to Mars."},{"time":186167,"text":"All this was done by hand,\nwith slide rules."},{"time":188309,"text":"The little Orion ship,"},{"time":189897,"text":"and what it would take\nto do what Orion does with chemicals:"},{"time":192773,"text":"you have a ship the size\nof the Empire State Building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":195334,"text":"NASA had no interest;\nthey tried to kill the project."},{"time":197838,"text":"The people who supported it\nwere the Air Force,"},{"time":200061,"text":"which meant that it was all secret."},{"time":201759,"text":"And that's why when you get something\ndeclassified, that's what it looks like."},{"time":205463,"text":"Military weapon versions\nthat carried hydrogen bombs"},{"time":208003,"text":"that could destroy half the planet."},{"time":209708,"text":"There's another version there that sends\nretaliatory strikes at the Soviet Union."},{"time":213556,"text":"This is the really secret stuff:"},{"time":215112,"text":"how to get directed energy explosions."},{"time":217248,"text":"So you're sending the energy\nof a nuclear explosion --"},{"time":219821,"text":"not like just a stick of dynamite,\nbut you're directing it at the ship."},{"time":223207,"text":"And this is still a very active subject."},{"time":225495,"text":"It's quite dangerous,"},{"time":226725,"text":"but I believe it's better to have\ndangerous things in the open"},{"time":229702,"text":"than think you're going\nto keep them secret."}]},{"cues":[{"time":231782,"text":"This is what happened\nat 600 microseconds."},{"time":233862,"text":"The Air Force started\nto build smaller models"},{"time":236661,"text":"and actually started doing this."},{"time":238379,"text":"The guys in La Jolla said,\n\"We've got to get started now.\""},{"time":241126,"text":"They built a high-explosive\npropelled model."},{"time":243550,"text":"These are stills from\nfilm footage that was saved"},{"time":247296,"text":"by someone who was supposed\nto destroy it but didn't,"},{"time":249875,"text":"and kept it in their basement\nfor the last 40 years."},{"time":252337,"text":"So, these are three-pound charges of C4;"},{"time":254277,"text":"that's about 10 times\nwhat the guy had in his shoes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":256974,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":258178,"text":"This is Ed Day putting --"},{"time":259624,"text":"So each of these coffee cans\nhas three pounds of C4 in it."},{"time":262897,"text":"They're building a system that ejects\nthese at quarter-second intervals."},{"time":267057,"text":"That's my dad in the sport coat there,\nholding the briefcase."},{"time":270359,"text":"So, they had a lot of fun doing this."},{"time":272511,"text":"But no children were allowed;"},{"time":274020,"text":"my dad could tell me he was building\na spaceship and going to go to Saturn,"},{"time":277647,"text":"but he could not say\nanything more about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279789,"text":"So all my life I have wanted\nto find this stuff out,"},{"time":282421,"text":"and spent the last four years\ntracking these old guys down."},{"time":285397,"text":"These are stills from the video."},{"time":286948,"text":"Jeff Bezos kindly, yesterday,\nsaid he'll put this video up"},{"time":289751,"text":"on the Amazon site --\nsome little clip of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":292167,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":293199,"text":"So, thanks to him."},{"time":294480,"text":"They got quite serious\nabout the engineering of this."},{"time":297100,"text":"The size of that mass, for us,"},{"time":299145,"text":"is really large technology in a way\nwe're never going to go back to."},{"time":303097,"text":"If you saw the 1959 --"},{"time":304875,"text":"this is what it would feel\nlike in the passenger compartment;"},{"time":307759,"text":"that's acceleration profile."}]},{"cues":[{"time":309156,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":310188,"text":"And pulse-system yield:\nwe're looking at 20-kiloton yield"},{"time":314065,"text":"for an effective thrust\nof 10 million newtons."},{"time":316400,"text":"Well, here we have a little problem,\nthe radiation doses at the crew station:"},{"time":320061,"text":"700 rads per shot."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322832,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":324563,"text":"Fission yields during development:"},{"time":326340,"text":"they were hoping to get\nclean bombs; they didn't."},{"time":329670,"text":"Eyeburn: this is what happens\nto the people in Miami who are looking up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333950,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335398,"text":"Personnel compartment noise: that's\nnot too bad; it's very low frequencies,"},{"time":338977,"text":"it's basically like these sub-woofers."},{"time":340819,"text":"And now we have ground-hazard assessments\nwhen you have a blow-up on the pad."},{"time":344477,"text":"Finally, at the very end in 1964,\nNASA steps in and says,"},{"time":347429,"text":"\"OK, we'll support a feasibility study\nfor a small version"},{"time":351022,"text":"that could be launched with Saturn Vs\nin sections and pieced together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":355146,"text":"So this is what NASA did,"},{"time":357195,"text":"getting an eight-man version\nthat would go to Mars."},{"time":362170,"text":"They liked it because the guys could\nkind of live there and be like,"},{"time":365390,"text":"\"It's like living in a submarine.\""},{"time":367040,"text":"This is crew compartment."},{"time":368326,"text":"It switches, so what's\nupside down is right side up"},{"time":370733,"text":"when you go to artificial gravity mode."},{"time":372620,"text":"The scientists were still\ngoing to go along;"},{"time":374706,"text":"they would take seven astronauts\nand seven scientists."},{"time":377255,"text":"This is a 20-man version\nfor going to Jupiter:"},{"time":379431,"text":"bunks, storm cellars, exercise room."},{"time":381227,"text":"You know, it was going\nto be a nice, long trip."}]},{"cues":[{"time":383898,"text":"The Air Force version:\nhere we have a military version."},{"time":388111,"text":"This is the kind of stuff\nthat's not been declassified,"},{"time":390725,"text":"just that people managed to sneak\nhome and after, you know,"},{"time":393527,"text":"on their deathbed,\nbasically, gave me that."},{"time":397074,"text":"The sort of artist conceptions."},{"time":398596,"text":"These are basically\nPowerPoint presentations"},{"time":400802,"text":"given to the Air Force 40 years ago."},{"time":402887,"text":"Look at the little guys there\noutside the vehicle."},{"time":407552,"text":"And one part of NASA was interested in it,"},{"time":410544,"text":"but the headquarters in NASA,\nthey killed the project."},{"time":414668,"text":"So finally, at the end,"},{"time":417074,"text":"we can see the thing followed\nits sort of design path right up to 1965,"},{"time":422315,"text":"and then all those paths came to a halt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424290,"text":"Results: none."},{"time":425775,"text":"This project is hereby terminated."},{"time":427803,"text":"So that's the end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429705,"text":"All I can say in closing is:"},{"time":431330,"text":"we heard yesterday that one of the 10\nbad things that could happen to us"},{"time":435657,"text":"is an asteroid with our name on it."},{"time":438271,"text":"And one of the bad things\nthat could happen to NASA"},{"time":440684,"text":"is if that asteroid shows up\nwith our name on it nine months out,"},{"time":443823,"text":"and everybody says,"},{"time":445442,"text":"\"Well, what are we going to do?\""},{"time":447019,"text":"And Orion is really one\nof the only, if not the only,"},{"time":449986,"text":"off-the-shelf technologies\nthat could do something."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454091,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":455966,"text":"So I'm going to tell you\nthe good news and the bad news."},{"time":458624,"text":"The good news is that NASA has a small,\nsecret contingency-plan division"},{"time":464399,"text":"that is looking at this, trying\nto keep knowledge of Orion preserved"},{"time":468962,"text":"in the event of such a misfortune."},{"time":471034,"text":"Maybe keep a few little\nbombs of plutonium on the side."},{"time":474066,"text":"That's the good news."},{"time":475241,"text":"The bad news is, when I got\nin contact with these people"},{"time":477892,"text":"to try and get some documents\nfrom them, they went crazy"},{"time":481003,"text":"because I had all this stuff\nthat they don't have,"},{"time":483374,"text":"and NASA purchased 1,759 pages\nof this stuff from me."},{"time":488443,"text":"So that's the state we're at;\nit's not very good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491150,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":492436,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}